tags.description: Named in honor of Major General John C Fremont. Camp Fremont was established by the US Army in 1917 as a 25,000 acre training ground for soldiers headed to France in World War I. This small park, with a similar name contains several war memorials.
tags.name: Camp Fremont Park

tags.description: A small half acre park. Home to The Tall Tree (the Sequoia Sempervirens, or Coast Redwood) that gave Palo Alto its name.
tags.name: El Palo Alto Park
